  "texts": [
    "Vision Transformers (ViTs) can be particularly beneficial to fossil image analysis due to their ability to dissect images into constituent patches and process them through selfattention mechanisms.",
    "For each patch, the mechanism computes attention scores that reflect its relevance compared to other patches, allowing the model to focus on salient features and relationships across the image, thereby enhancing its understanding and representation of fossil data (Zhang et al. 2021).",
    "Self-attention enables ViTs to differentiate between fossil region-of-interest and the background for segmentation, precisely delineating the boundaries of fossilized remains.",
    "In classification tasks, the global perspective afforded by ViTs helps recognize subtle morphological features that distinguish different fossil species or categorize them into broader taxonomic groups.",
    "Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) have been impactful in various fields (e.g., chemistry) by leveraging the inherent graph structure of data."
  ],
